UN Secretary General Kofi Annan expressed deep concern over Nepal's democracy crisis as King Gyanendra dismissed the government and imposed a state of emergency.
The US, EU, Japan, and UK condemned the king's actions, urging a swift return to democracy.
India seeks to maintain stability and historical ties with Nepal, while China remains neutral.
Human rights abuses persist amidst the Maoist insurgency.
Gyanendra named a new Cabinet to restore democracy, facing international backlash.
China respects Nepal's sovereignty, emphasizing internal affairs.
Pakistan supports Nepal's unity and hopes for SAARC Summit rescheduling.
Non-intervention principles guide Pakistan-Nepal relations.
